<h1>"Hello, ${message}" Explained</h1>

A minimal, templated, Tapestry application needs only three files. For example:

<ul>
    <li><strong>HelloWorldExplained.tml</strong> An (X)HTML template for the /helloworldexplained page. Tapestry
        templates can contain any well-formed (X)HTML markup.
    </li>
    <li><strong>HelloWorldExplained.java</strong> A page class associated with the template. Here it merely provides a
        <em>username</em> property that the template can access.
    </li>
    <li><strong>web.xml</strong> A servlet application deployment descriptor which installs Tapestry as a servlet
        filter.
    </li>
</ul>

In this page we also use two <em>components</em>:

<ul>
    <li><strong>PageLink</strong> which is a core Tapestry component that outputs an HTML link to another page.</li>
    <li><strong>SourceCodeDisplay</strong> which is a custom component provided by JumpStart to output source files as
        HTML.
    </li>
</ul>

